Guards in v5 are pure predicates declared once inside `setup({ guards })` and referenced by string from any transition's `guard` slot. Each guard receives `{ context, event }` and returns a boolean. Centralising them gets you reuse, string-based references in the machine body, and clean type inference — since `setup` knows your event union, the guard parameter types are inferred automatically.

