In XState v5, register a `fromPromise(...)` actor in `setup.actors` and reference it by name from `invoke.src`. When the promise resolves, `onDone` fires with typed `event.output`. When it rejects, `onError` fires with `event.error`. Both transitions can carry `assign` actions that capture the result into context.

