`sendTo(target, event)` is the v5 replacement for v4's `send(event, { to })`. `target` is either a string id (the id you used when spawning or invoking the child) or a function that reads the actor ref from context. `sendParent(event)` dispatches an event from a child up to its parent actor — handy for replies. Both should carry typed events so the receiver's `on:` handlers get narrowed properly.

```ts
