`always` evaluates on entry and on every context update. The context is usually the cleanest thing to guard on, because at evaluation time there isn't an incoming user event — only the assign that triggered the re-evaluation. The idiomatic pattern is: stash what you need into context in the `on:` action, then guard `always` off context.

```ts
import { setup, assign } from 'xstate';

type Ctx = { lastValue: number };
type Ev = { type: 'SET'; value: number };

