    O.chain((o) => O.fromNullable(o.a)),
    O.chain((a) => O.fromNullable(a.b)),
    O.chain((b) => O.fromNullable(b.c)),
    O.getOrElse<string>(() => 'fallback'),
  );
```

The JS syntax is shorter, but the `Option` version composes with any `A -> Option<B>` function — including validators and parsers that go beyond simple null checks.

