    debounceTime(300),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    switchMap((q: string) => searchPlaces$(q))
  );
}
```

Using `mergeMap` here would be the classic bug — responses can arrive out of order and overwrite fresher results.

The three-operator stack decouples *when* you search (after the user pauses) from *what* you search for (unique values only) from *how* you handle overlapping async requests (always keep the latest). Put another way: `debounceTime` smooths the burst of events, `distinctUntilChanged` collapses no-op re-emissions, and `switchMap` enforces "one inner observable at a time — newer wins."

```ts
