  return term$.pipe(
    debounceTime(200),
    distinctUntilChanged(),
    switchMap((q: string) => filterEmployees$(q))
  );
}
```

`switchMap` subscribes to whatever inner observable its projection function returns. When the outer observable emits a new value while the previous inner is still active, `switchMap` calls `unsubscribe` on that previous inner subscription before subscribing to the new one. For a network-backed inner observable that hooks into `AbortController`, that unsubscribe aborts the HTTP request. Net effect: only the most-recent inner observable ever emits to the downstream.

