`forkJoin` waits for every input observable to *complete* before
emitting. A `BehaviorSubject` never completes on its own (you'd have to
call `.complete()`), so threading one through `forkJoin` produces an
output that never fires. Either swap it for a one-shot `of()` / HTTP
source, or take one value with `first()` / `take(1)` so it completes.

```ts
