`mergeMap` gives us interleaved completion (fast endpoints finish first); the cap of 10 keeps the downstream receivers from being hammered.

- `concatMap(fn)` — strictly one inner at a time, ordered. Slowest.
- `switchMap(fn)` — only the LATEST outer value matters; inflight inner gets cancelled.
- `mergeMap(fn, n)` — up to `n` inners in flight concurrently, interleaved results.

