`retry(n)` is the positional shorthand: up to `n` resubscriptions with zero delay. `retry({ count, delay })` supplements `count` with a `delay` callback so each retry waits for the returned observable to emit (typically `timer(ms)`). In v7+ the object form is the canonical way to express backoff — `retryWhen` is deprecated.

```ts
import { Observable, timer } from "rxjs";
import { retry } from "rxjs/operators";

